Normalise data using different methods: log, power, and root, with a different number of parameters to find out which one transforms the data into a normal-ish set.

Source: R/transformations.R
transform_data.Rd

Normalise data using different methods: log, power, and root, with a different number of parameters to find out which one transforms the data into a normal-ish set.

transform_data(
  data,
  feature = "DATA",
  alpha = 0.05,
  index = NULL,
  transf_vals = c(2, exp(1), 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10),
  plots_prefix = "HIST",
  digits = 6
)

Arguments

data

original data
feature

feature name
alpha

significance level
index

index of the current feature
transf_vals

transformation values
plots_prefix

prefix for plots with or without path
digits

significant digits to compare p-values of transformations

Value

transformed record

Examples

set.seed(123)
data <- rnorm(100, 5)
transform_data(2 ^ data, "EXP_2")
